subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen (
Fig. 40
) yellow with sparse silvery white pruinescence; tergite 2 with a pair of blackish brown lateral posterior bands; tergites 3–6 each with a black median spot, confluent with black posterior band on tergites 3–5. Male genitalia (
Figs. 81–85
): protandrium circular, with a long narrow furcated ventral process; epandrium nearly triangular in posterior view, surstylus broad, hairy, digitiform; hypandrium with a narrow, furcated ventral process, hypandrial apodeme distinct; gonopod columniform; aedeagus without distinct apical incision, consisting of a pair of dorsal sclerites, with a pair of lateral median teeth, a pair of ventral teeth and a pair of dorsal teeth.
